    h1 Privacy Policy
    h2 1. Scope of this Privacy Policy
    p "Wonderflow" places great importance on the confidentiality of your personal information. The purpose of this policy is to explain how we collect, use, and disclose the personal information you may provide to us or that we may otherwise hold about you, and aims to comply with Canadian federal and provincial privacy protection laws.

    h2 2. Acceptance
    p By using this website, you signify your acceptance of this policy. Similarly, by submitting your personal information to us, you agree that it will be governed by this policy.
    p Please note that this policy only applies to our websites and not to the websites of other companies or organizations linked to ours. Wonderflow does not endorse and is not responsible for those linked websites.
    p Your consent may be withdrawn at any time, subject to legal and contractual restrictions and reasonable notice. Please note that if you choose to withdraw your consent, Wonderflow may not be able to provide certain services.

    h2 3. Changes to the Policy
    p We reserve the right to change this policy at any time by posting the updated terms on our website. We therefore encourage you to review this policy regularly.

    h2 4. Collection of Your Personal Information
    p Wonderflow only collects the information you have consented to provide. We do not sell, rent, or share your personal information except as described below.
    p Wonderflow limits the collection of your personal information to what is necessary to establish, manage, and maintain our relationship with you. For example, personal information may be collected during registration, newsletter subscriptions, or when submitting questions, comments, or suggestions, and may include—without limitation—identifying information such as your first and last name, gender, date of birth, home address, phone number, email address, and professional information such as your current job and sector.
    p Generally, we collect this personal information directly from you. However, we may also collect information about you from external sources with your consent or, where permitted by law, without your consent.

    h2 5. Cookies
    p Your use of this website allows Wonderflow to automatically collect certain user profile information, which may include your computer's IP address, the operating system you use, your Internet service provider, the date and time you accessed this website, the website you visited before linking to ours, and the content you viewed and downloaded from our site.
    p To do this, our website, like most websites, uses cookies stored on your computer when you visit. We use this information to tailor our website to your preferences, including the ads shown, and to compile statistics about the usage and viewing of our website in order to improve it.
    p As with most Internet browsers, you can delete cookies from your hard drive, block new cookies, or receive a warning before cookies are saved. Doing so, however, may affect your ability to use our website, and you may not have access to all its functions. We encourage you to consult Ads Settings, the Network Advertising Initiative, and your browser’s help section for more information.

