    h2 6. Use of Your Personal Information
    p Wonderflow may use your personal information for the following purposes:
    p to identify you as a user of our website and client, if applicable; to establish and maintain our business relationship with you; to continuously provide you with services; to improve our product and service offerings, including this website; to communicate with you when you submit questions, comments, or suggestions; to provide information about our activities, products, and services that may interest you; to prevent errors and fraud; and to comply with legal obligations. Wonderflow may also use your personal information to compile statistics. However, these statistics will not allow you to be identified.
    p Your personal information will not be used for purposes other than those listed above without your consent, unless permitted or required by law.

    h2 7. Disclosure of Your Personal Information
    p Wonderflow recognizes that, except as stated below, disclosing your personal information to third parties requires your consent.
    p Access to this information within Wonderflow does not require your consent but is strictly limited to those whose job duties require it.
    p Wonderflow may also share your information, without your consent, with agents, representatives, consultants, data processors, service providers, and others who need it for Wonderflow’s business activities or to assist with administration (promotions, tech support, etc.).
    p Wonderflow may also disclose information about you in its files as authorized or required by law without your consent.
    p In each case, Wonderflow will strive not to disclose more personal information than necessary for the situation.
    p Please note that if the third party to whom Wonderflow discloses information is located in a foreign country, local laws may allow access to your personal information without your consent.

    h2 8. Security Measures
    p Wonderflow implements reasonable security measures appropriate to the sensitivity of the personal information held. These measures are intended to protect your personal data from loss, theft, or unauthorized access, disclosure, copying, use, or modification.
    p We also take reasonable steps to ensure that personal data collected is accurate and complete. However, it is your responsibility to notify us of any changes to your personal information.

    h2 9. Questions and Requests
    p Any questions or concerns regarding this Policy or about the collection, use, or disclosure of your personal information, including access or correction requests, must be submitted in writing by email to: info@wonderflow.ca
    p You have the right to access and obtain a copy of the personal information held about you by Wonderflow. You can also request corrections of inaccurate, incomplete, or ambiguous information and the deletion of information that is not justified by the purpose of the file.
    p Wonderflow will respond to each access and correction request within 30 days of receiving the written request. If Wonderflow cannot provide access or correct the information, it will inform you of the reasons and any possible recourse.
